revision.text:
'''Abortion in Tuvalu''' is only legal if the [[abortion]] will save the mother's life.<ref name=UN>{{cite book|title=Abortion Policies: Oman to Zimbabwe|date=2001|publisher=United Nations Publications|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3iNmQIP7S2AC&dq=abortion+in+vanuatu&source=gbs_navlinks_s|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref> If an abortion is performed on a woman for any other reason, the violator is subject to ten years in prison.<ref name=UN /> A woman who performs a [[self-induced abortion]] may be imprisoned for life.<ref name=UN />

