'''Mohammed Aboul-Fotouh Hassab''' was an Egyptian gastro-intestinal surgeon. He is known for the description of his operation [[Hassab’s decongestion operation]] for the treatment of [[oesophageal varices]] as a result of [[portal hypertension]].  Hassab was one of the surgery professors in medicine school at Alexandria University in Egypt.

==Activities==
*[[Hassab's decongestion operation|Hassab Operation]], which is the treatment of bleeding esophageal varices, is taught in surgery world books.

